description:
Use this function if you are asked to get a list of recently used files. Input: optional number of files to return. Output: an object describing the result of the operation. The files are sorted with the most recently used files appearing first.

Return value:
{
"role": "tool", // Required constant field
"status": "success" | "error",
"files": [ { "path": "string", "type": "integer" } ], // Array of objects with file path and type
"error_message": "string | null" // Error details if status = 'error'
}

Example function call parameter: { "limit": 5 }

Example successful response:
{
"role": "tool",
"status": "success",
"files": [ { "path": "/home/user/file1.txt", "type": 0 }, { "path": "/home/user/file2.docx", "type": 1 } ],
"error_message": null
}

Example error response:
{
"role": "tool",
"status": "error",
"files": [],
"error_message": "Recent files history not available."
}
